list-item.p:
                  Introducing best practices for coding. Students are introduced to best practices for accessibility. For example, here are a few best practices:
                     

using alt attributes, which provide screen-reader users with text to understand an image (e.g., “Meteor Valley Animal Rescue logo”)
                     
                     

using links to skip navigation, which allow users to bypass long, repetitive navigation bars
                     
                     

using descriptive links, which allow users to identify a link out of context (e.g., “read our product guide” rather than “click here”)
                     
                     

applying techniques to design for usability not only for sighted users but for users with visual impairments (Leporini & Paternò, 2008) and other disabilities
